    {
      "id": "26.11.5-1",
      "type": "provision",
      "section": "26.11.5",
      "text": "**26.11.5 Flexible Buildings or Other Structures** For flexible buildings or other structures as defined in Section 26.2, the gust-effect factor shall be calculated by",
      "cross_references": [
        "26.2"
      ],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0,
        "x_end": 1,
        "y_start": 0,
        "y_end": 1
      },
      "column": "right",
      "heading": true,
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "26.11.5-2",
      "type": "formula",
      "section": "26.11.5",
      "text": "Gf = 0.925(1 + 1.7Iz√(gQ²Q̄² + gR²R²))/(1 + 1.7gvIz) (26.11-10)",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0,
        "x_end": 1,
        "y_start": 0,
        "y_end": 1
      },
      "column": "right",
      "expression": "Gf = 0.925(1 + 1.7Iz√(gQ²Q̄² + gR²R²))/(1 + 1.7gvIz)",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "26.11.5-3",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.5",
      "text": "The background peak factors gQ and gv shall be taken as 3.4, and the resonant peak factor gR is",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0,
        "x_end": 1,
        "y_start": 0,
        "y_end": 1
      },
      "column": "right",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "26.11.5-4",
      "type": "formula",
      "section": "26.11.5",
      "text": "gR = √(2 ln(3,600n1)) + 0.577/√(2 ln(3,600n1)) (26.11-11)",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0,
        "x_end": 1,
        "y_start": 0,
        "y_end": 1
      },
      "column": "right",
      "expression": "gR = √(2 ln(3,600n1)) + 0.577/√(2 ln(3,600n1))",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "26.11.5-5",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.5",
      "text": "The background response factor, Q̄, and the intensity of turbulence at height z̄, Iz, are defined in Section 26.11.4. The resonant response factor is",
      "cross_references": [
        "26.11.4"
      ],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0,
        "x_end": 1,
        "y_start": 0,
        "y_end": 1
      },
      "column": "right",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "26.11.5-6",
      "type": "formula",
      "section": "26.11.5",
      "text": "R = √(1/β × RnRhRB(0.53 + 0.47RL)) (26.11-12)",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0,
        "x_end": 1,
        "y_start": 0,
        "y_end": 1
      },
      "column": "right",
      "expression": "R = √(1/β × RnRhRB(0.53 + 0.47RL))",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "26.11.5-7",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.5",
      "text": "where n1 is the fundamental natural frequency, and β is the damping ratio, fraction of critical (e.g., for 2% use 0.02 in the equation).",
